#lang scribble/manual

@title{Game Show}

Use these questions during Game Show time. You can ask any/all the questions in each day's section.

@section{Monday}

@itemlist[@item{@bold{How do you move your sprite?}
                    @itemlist[@item{@italic{By using the up, down, right, and left arrows.}}]}
          @item{@bold{What is the objective of the game?}
                    @itemlist[@item{@italic{Staying alive by eating food items.}}]}
          @item{@bold{How do you eat the food?}
                    @itemlist[@item{@italic{Get close to the item and press spacebar on the keyboard.}}]}
          @item{@bold{What key do you press to add the start icon to your code?}
                    @itemlist[@item{@italic{The equal sign.}}]}
          @item{@bold{Name 3 character sprite options.}
                    @itemlist[@item{@italic{Monkey, elephant, hippo, or kangaroo.}}]}]


@section{Tuesday}

@itemlist[@item{@bold{Name 2 food sprite options.}
                    @itemlist[@item{@italic{Apple, banana, fish, grapes, onion, potato, or tomato.}}]}
          @item{@bold{How do you heal your friends?}
                    @itemlist[@item{@italic{Get close to them and press the H key to activate your healing powers.}}]}
          @item{@bold{What is the lang line needed for today's code?}
                    @itemlist[@item{@italic{Could be: healer-zoo-foods, healer-zoo-friends, or healer-zoo-enemies.}}]}
          @item{@bold{What does the question mark image do in your game?}
                    @itemlist[@item{@italic{It chooses a random image and uses it in your game.}}]}
          @item{@bold{What is the name of the port (hole) where you plug in a mouse?}
                    @itemlist[@item{@italic{USB port.}}]}]

@section{Wednesday}

@itemlist[@item{@bold{Name 3 friend sprite options.}
                    @itemlist[@item{@italic{Zookeeper, monkey, elephant, hippo, kangaroo, or penguin.}}]}
          @item{@bold{How do you add multiple of one sprite?}
                    @itemlist[@item{@italic{Wrap it around parentheses and add a number next to it.}}]}
          @item{@bold{Can you have the same sprite be a your character, a food, a friend, and an enemy?}
                    @itemlist[@item{@italic{YES!}}]}
          @item{@bold{What are the ways of losing the game?}
                    @itemlist[@item{@italic{By not eating enough food, or by getting hit by enemies.}}]}
          @item{@bold{Input is a way for a human to give information to a computer, what devices do we use for this?}
                    @itemlist[@item{@italic{Mouse/touchpad, keyboard, microphone, etc.}}]}]

@section{Thursday}

@itemlist[@item{@bold{How can you color a sprite?}
                    @itemlist[@item{@italic{By wrapping it in parentheses and adding a color next to it.}}]}
          @item{@bold{Name all the different colors available.}
                    @itemlist[@item{@italic{Red, orange, yellow, green, blue, and purple.}}]}
          @item{@bold{How many health points do you lose when an enemy hits you?}
                    @itemlist[@item{@italic{10 points.}}]}
          @item{@bold{What is the visual diffence between a parentheses and a bracket?}
                    @itemlist[@item{@italic{A parentheses is round and the bracket has straight edges.}}]}
          @item{@bold{Output is a way for a computer to give a human information, what devices do we use for this?}
                    @itemlist[@item{@italic{Monitor/projector, speakers/headphones, printer, etc.}}]}]